==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dorr
<hw>Dorr</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The dorbeetle; also, a
drone or an idler. See 1st <er>Dor</er>.</def> <rj><au>Robynson (More's
Utopia).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dorr</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dorr
<hw>Dorr</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To deceive.
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> See <er>Dor</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To deafen with noise.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dorrfly</ent>⟦br⟧
